Andrei Sakharov was a physicist who helped develop the Soviet hydrogen bomb .
He later gained widespread fame as a human rights advocate and the 1979 winner of the Nobel Peace Prize .
His constant criticism irked the Kremlin .
In 1980 he criticized the invasion of Afghanistan and Breznev exiled him to Gorky .
Gorbachev freed him in 1986 .
Sakharov praised Gorbachev on foreign affairs , but criticized his economic policies .
Sakharov was elected to the Soviet Congress of People 's Deputies in April 1989 .
Sakharov died suddenly on 14 December 1989 .
His obituary , signed by Gorbachev , was tantamount to public apology .
